# ANTI-SLOP FRONTEND — ELITE ANTI-AI VERSION
# Nothing generic. Nothing repeatable. Nothing with AI aesthetics.
# Design = Engineering. Every decision is intentional.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I. ABSOLUTE PRINCIPLE: "NO GENERIC, NO DEFAULTS"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- It is forbidden to generate any interface that can be confused with:
  - templates
  - common landing pages
  - UI generated by non-creative AI models
  - generic "corporate SaaS" structures
  - pastel palettes without intention
  - cliché hero gradients (especially purple-to-blue on white)
  - default symmetric spacing like bootstrap

- ALL aesthetics must be unique:
  Every output MUST have a **Concept Hook**
  (1 unrepeatable aesthetic idea documented in PR).

Examples of Concept Hooks:
- Diagonal kinetic grid
- Typographic collage layout
- Noise-driven texture atmosphere
- Cinematic shadow layering
- Brutalist grid-break fold
- Retro-stencil display typography
- Compositional anatomy inspired by Swiss posters, Bauhaus, Memphis synthesis, etc.

The hook must be visible and verifiable.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II. TYPOGRAPHY — PROFESSIONAL ANTI-AI LEVEL
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Forbidden: Inter, Roboto, Poppins, Montserrat, Space Grotesk, DM Sans, system-ui.
  (These fonts are detectors of generic AI aesthetics.)
- Always use typography with character:
  - display with strong personality
  - refined body with editorial or technical intention

- Every font pairing must meet:
  - expressive contrast
  - clear motive (editorial, brutalist, retro-futuristic, etc.)
  - license + accessibility test
  - mandatory tokenization (type.family.*, type.weight.*, type.tracking.*)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
III. COLOR — NO HARD-CODED, NO CLICHÉS, NO TEMPLATES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Every color comes from DS tokens.
- Forbidden:
  - Purple/blue with white SaaS template style.
  - Basic linear gradients without texture or intention.
  - Very common AI palettes (generic pastel, beige+purple, neon+black 90s without coherence).

- The palette must have:
  - Strong conceptual dominant.
  - 1–2 memorable accents.
  - Rationale: why it exists, what it communicates.

- Each color must have a purpose:
  - Atmosphere
  - Signal
  - Hierarchy
  - Accent
  - Emotion

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IV. MOTION — INTENTIONAL AND NON-TEMPLATE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Default generated animations are forbidden.
- Only animations with the following are allowed:
  - narrative intention
  - studied rhythm
  - use of DS easing tokens (not default)
  - clear choreography (stagger, reveal, displacement, manual parallax)

- No redundant micro-interactions.
- Motion must sustain the aesthetics, not adorn it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
V. SPATIAL COMPOSITION — NO AI "PERFECT GRID"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The layout cannot be predictable.
AI tends to:

- center everything
- use symmetric grid
- place hero and CTA predictably
- repeat "safe" proportions

Therefore, these rules are mandatory:

- At least ONE pattern must be broken:
  - non-parallel alignments
  - controlled overflow
  - diagonal directions
  - calculated asymmetry
  - visual collage
  - extreme negative space

- Even so, everything must maintain semantic accessibility.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VI. COMPONENTS — NOTHING GENERATED, EVERYTHING ENGINEERED
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A visual component must have:

- Clear and documented API
- tokens for spacing, color, typography, motion
- visual story
- aesthetic rationale
- DO NOT repeat UI structure used previously in similar outputs
- DO NOT look derived from a generic UI kit

If shadcn is used:
- composition > modification
- tokenized styles
- forbidden to copy shadcn templates without modifying composition and aesthetics

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VII. TEXTURES AND MATERIALS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To escape AI aesthetics:

- Introduce texture or materiality:
  - grain overlay
  - mesh gradients
  - geometric noise
  - shape clusters
  - paper/dust simulation
  - fluid distortion

All textures must come from licensed assets.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VIII. PERFORMANCE AND A11Y (PROD LEVEL)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Everything must maintain:
  - LCP <= 2.5s
  - INP <= 200ms
  - CLS <= 0.1

- Accessibility:
  - contrast ≥ 4.5
  - reading order intact even if the layout is experimental

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IX. FORBIDDEN (AUTO-FAIL)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Any visual reference that looks like:
  - default purple gradient
  - generic "modern minimal" UI
  - symmetric centered grid without intention
  - predictable hero
  - default parallax
  - AI trendy fonts
  - uniform spacing in all directions
  - iconography without character

- No interface can look like an average template marketplace website.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
X. PR CHECKLIST — AESTHETIC AND TECHNICAL
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Every delivery must include:

- Tone + Concept Hook
- Complete Token Mapping
- Visual rationale (2–5 lines)
- A11y evidence
- Performance evidence
- Confirmation: "No generic elements / no AI patterns"
- Design Engineering Approval

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
XI. EXCEPTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Only per ticket with complete rationale.
- Mandatory review by Design Owner.
- Expires in 30 days.
